message.content:
It is difficult to generalize the interests and obsessions of all kids in Malawi, as their preferences can vary greatly. However, like kids in many other parts of the world, some common obsessions among Malawian children may include:

1. Technology and gadgets: With the increasing availability of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices, many kids in Malawi, like elsewhere, may be obsessed with technology and spend a significant amount of time on social media, gaming, or watching videos.

2. Music and dance: Malawi has a vibrant music scene, and many kids may be obsessed with local and international music. They may spend time learning dance moves, singing along to their favorite songs, or even aspiring to become musicians themselves.

3. Sports: Football (soccer) is hugely popular in Malawi, and many kids may be obsessed with playing or watching the sport. They may idolize local or international football players and spend time discussing matches, collecting football cards, or playing video games related to the sport.

4. Fashion and celebrities: Like kids in many other countries, some Malawian children may be obsessed with fashion trends and celebrities. They may follow popular fashion influencers, try to emulate their styles, or keep up with the latest celebrity news.
